history.content: Yes. CS 61A over the summer is high workload and will definitely take a lot of time and effort, but it's doable and many students come in without prior programming experience. The class doesn't assume prior knowledge of any language/topic, but it does move through difficult topics quickly. I would recommend not taking any other classes on top of it though.
I was wondering if it would be doable to take cs 61A over summer and get an A or A-, considering that the only background I have is working with C++ and mathlab couple years ago? Thank you.
